<p>I've looked everywhere and am unable to find a solution.</p>  <p>I want to redirect several folders (and all of their contents, including subfolders) to the root of the website.</p>  <p>Example of <strong>what should happen</strong>:</p>  <pre><code>http://www.domain.com/folder/ -&gt; http://www.domain.com/ http://www.domain.com/folder/subfolder/ -&gt; http://www.domain.com/ </code></pre>  <p>Example of <strong>what happens now</strong>:</p>  <pre><code>http://www.domain.com/folder/ -&gt; http://www.domain.com/ (works!) http://www.domain.com/folder/subfolder/ -&gt; http://www.domain.com/subfolder/ (doesn't work!) </code></pre>  <p>What's wrong?</p>  <pre><code>RewriteEngine On RewriteRule ^folder/(.*)$ http://www.domain.com/ [R=301,NC,L] </code></pre>